Rick Giaimo, Senior Software Architect at Nevo,
brings a deep understanding of the subtleties of excellent software design and implementation.  Rick was the Chief Architect at Kronos, and Elsevier MDL, and Molecular Simulations.

Like everyone at Nevo, Rick is deeply involved not only in the abstract design of applications, but in their detailed development as well.  Rick firmly believes in the principle that hands-on development is critical to resolving the subtle issues that distinguish great software from average.  Consequently, Rick has been deeply involved in building core components.

At Nevo he has been a key contributor to the architecture and implementation of the EMHome solution, guiding all aspects of the complex building model engine.  Similar to his work on Molecular Simulation, the EMHome building model creates a complex, dynamic, and highly interactive model of energy consumption, and dissipation for residential structures, enabling home owners to identify the best opportunities for both energy and cost savings in their homes.

<p>Mr. Giaimo earned a BS degree in Electrical Engineering and Computer Science from MIT.



